<p>VIPER, the Visual Project Explorer, is a unique open science application developed by 
<a href="https://openknowledgemaps.org" target="_blank">Open Knowledge Maps</a> that 
focuses on the discovery of research project results. VIPER enables you to systematically 
explore a project's output and to understand its impact in different areas.

<h3>Acknowledgements</h3>
<p>
VIPER is made possible thanks to funding received from <a href="https://openaire.eu" target="_blank">OpenAIRE</a>, 
a key infrastructure that enables the European transition to open science. We would also like to thank our data providers  
<a href="https://openaire.eu" target="_blank">OpenAIRE</a> (all metadata), 
<a href="https://crossref.org" target="_blank">CrossRef</a> (all citation data), 
and <a href="https://altmetric.com" target="_blank">Altmetric</a> (all other metrics data).
</p>

<h3>Note on the use of metrics</h3>
<p class="metric-info">
    Metrics are provided for indicative purposes only and cannot be used as-is in an evaluation.
    If you intend to use the metrics provided for evaluative purposes, consider relevant
    guidelines such as the <a href="http://www.leidenmanifesto.org/" target="_blank">Leiden Manifesto for Research Metrics</a>
</p>

